  "To the best of your knowledge, are you a referral or relative of a current Senior Government Official (SGO)(1) and/or do you currently hold, or have you held within the last five (5) years a SGO position? (1) SGO is a Government Official (Non-U.S.) or U.S. Public Official who occupies an influential position within a government entity and makes, or has the ability or authority to make, decisions for or on behalf of a government entity in relations to transactions, assets, funds, and/or direction of a government entity with relations to business with Citi. This includes U.S. Public Officials, Government Officials (Non-U.S.) and employees of self-regulatory organizations for the financial services industry (even if the self-regulatory organization is not a government-sponsored entity). Examples generally NOT considered SGOs include non-managerial police officers, firefighters, correctional officers, postal employees, clerical workers, teachers, librarians, and public transportation employees.": "",
  "To the best of your knowledge, are you a referral of a current Senior Commercial Person (SCP)(1)? (1) SCP is an employee of a commercial (i.e. non-governmental) business organization (other than a Citi employee) who occupies an influential position within a commercial business organization or makes, or has the ability or authority to make, decisions for or on behalf of a commercial business organization in relation to transactions, assets, funds, and/or direction of a commercial business organization in relation to business with Citi. Examples include: a Chief Executive Officer (CEO), the deputy of the CEO, a voting member of the Board of Directors (whether in an executive or non-executive capacity) of an organization; Chief Financial Officer, Chief Legal Officer or General Counsel, Chief Operating Officer, Treasurer, or other persons with similar levels of management responsibilities and authority, or an officer with responsibility to make decisions directing the investments, assets, or transactions for or on behalf of a commercial business organization.": "",
